  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2004-09-21",
    "date": "2004-12-20T16:52:19Z",
    "text": "Higher Education Preparation Program Act of 2004 - Directs the Secretary of Education to award: (1) a competitive grant to a nonprofit organization to develop a curriculum-based higher education preparation program curriculum for students in grades eight, nine, and ten; and (2) competitive grants to up to five State educational agencies to use such curriculum in a demonstration project for providing higher education preparation programs to students in such grades in middle and secondary schools."
